http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Union-Minister-to-hand-over-FACT-relief/article14016655.ece

Union Minister for Chemicals and Fertilizers Ananth Kumar will visit Kochi on February 8 to formally hand over Rs.1,000 crore in interim relief to Fertilizers and Chemicals Travancore Ltd (FACT). A formal function is being arranged on the sprawling Ambalamedu campus of the fertilizer company on the day to mark the occasion, company sources said.The visit of the Minister will be the beginning of a positive chapter for the financially-troubled public sector company as the loan implies revival of its fortunes. A spokesman for Save FACT Action Forum, a combine of trade unions at the company, who welcomed the Minister to Kochi said that the decision to provide a loan to FACT had come in the nick of time.The Board of Directors of FACT, which met in Delhi early this week, formally approved a memorandum of understanding with the Ministry of Finance for release of the money. The MoU was finalised after FACT authorities received a formal communication from the Finance ministry regarding the infusion of funds.